Got a new phone...I'm thinking of downloading some ring tones...Rock the Casbah (in honor of ashley) maybe?  oh well.  Nothing is going on this weekend.  But tomorrow night i'm going out to dinner for my mom's b-day..crap i still have to wrap her gift. 

Yesterday I took Matt to a baseball game.  It was really cute how he was teaching me all the positions for baseball... I must have sounded like a complete idiot...oh well..you know what else sucks? everytime Matt sees me i have crappy, and i mean CRAPPY hair days...it looked totally awesome today, but did i see matt? no of course not.  I look hot on the days i don't try and when i do try..let's not even go there.

I'm a loser home on a friday night because Megan and Kate are both babysitting. UGH. Now I'm just reading over my notes from class this week.

Lindsay came home from NJ (i'm surprised)...ugh..i think i have to see her tomorrow...NOOOOOOOO

that's enough for now..shower time

\m/

...basically not a lot.  
ugh so now school as started again and lucky me i have class with "wanna shoot some snakes" boy and his best friend.  When they walked into the class they had the biggest grin on their face when they saw me, i wanted to crawl into a hole and hide.  THen the girl next to me said that one of the guys was staring at me the whole class time! ahhhhhhhhhh.  But my reward for starting school was going out that night and seeing garden state with Matt.  Then i got a flat tire....yeah..I'll remember this first date.

I miss ashley soooo much.  I think we call eachother like 10 times a day but keeping missing each other.  Hopefully I will go down to UF to visit her soon.

Talked to Will tonight, he's sooooooo freakin' negative - it's unreal.

We are celebrating my mom's b-day this weekend...which reminds me, i need to get her a gift CRAP!!!

well i need to take a shower and get ready for bed

peace out

hahah i love watching the newlyweds..not because jessica is the dumbest person on this planet..but sadly.i watch it to see my old house and my old town...oh look they are at mcdonald's at the el camino shopping center! oh memories!

yeah it sucked. i got into one of those moods. the kind where you punish yourself in listening to a song that floods you with sooo many emotions and you don't know what else to do but cry.  yeah that was me last nite.  i thought about will--the good, the bad and the ugly parts of him.  Damn him for being so fuckin hot.  i stole his driver's license..thinking then it was his motorcycle license.but now that i look at it..its his driver's license! ops. oh well. so yeah i cried a lot last nite. i kept saying i'm sorry to his picture.  i came to terms last nite that i still love that asshole.  i mean seriously there an hour doesn't go by that i dont think of him.  and sadly he doesn't know that.  i couldn't explain our relationship.  i mean this guy thought the world of me. i could come home looking like shit and this guy would tell me I was the most beautiful woman in the world and actually mean it.  god i miss the way he looked at me...i felt amazing just by him looking at me. I'll try to scan a photo of him later. i want to talk to him and explain why i left and how i compare every guy i meet to him.  i understand that will and i had this different kind of love for eachother..but it was still love..and i shouldn't compare sex with eric to making love with will..'cause there is a difference between making love and just having sex.

speaking of eric he wrote me an email today..i don't know what to make of it..they do say absence makes the heart grow fonder..but still..i think its a little much i've only known the guy for like a month(i'm talking about the last paragraph)

still can't eat. i don't know..i've just been in some sort of depression..not a major one..but i'm just not myself. and its not because eric left. i could care less i don't even miss him to be honest.

i see all these people at school who all know eachother and talk about memories and stuff and there i am just watching, sooo bad wanting to have someone i can relate to and talk about stuff that happened in high school or anything really.

i'm at this point right now where i feel like i can't relate to anyone..even eric. i know he likes me WAY more than i like him and i just can't relate to him. i've moved around a lot, experienced way more than many people my age have. and have done things i'm not proud of.

i know i won't find someone in the jax area..its just known..don't be friends with people born and raised here...they are a little..how do you say it.....HICKS!!!!

i guess i'll write later...i really don't want to type anymore
